Commentary: A gentle paced delivery to begin with! Length and outside off, left alone.

Another one on a length and around off, defended solidly.
Just outside off, no swing or seam for the bowler. Left alone.
Another one outside off, Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Nice and fine! Off the mark in style! This is on a length and around off, Abdullah Shafique just opens the face of the bat and guides it past the gully fielder and down to the third man fence.
Tosses it up nicely and on off, defended.
Floats it up on off, blocked.

FOUR! Two in a row! Shan is not short in confidence here! He skips down the track again, gets to the pitch and lofts it over mid on for another boundary.
Leach now pushes it through and the line is a lot straighter, this is worked to square leg.
On a length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms to this one.
Good length again and on off, Abdullah Shafique plays it to covers.

Flatter and on middle, not a lot of turn for Leach yet, defended.
Quicker and on middle, kept out.

A LOUD SHOUT AND GIVEN! Abdullah Shafique reviews just in time! Seems out though. OUT! The ball is clipping the leg pole and it remains umpire's call! Abdullah Shafique has to walk back and England strike early. Leach provides the breakthrough for them! This is angled into the pads. It lands and straightens just a touch. Abdullah Shafique plays outside the line. He misses and it hits his pad. A loud shout and the finger is raised. Pakistan though do not lose the review.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

NOT OUT! Impact was umpire's call! Not a bad review in the end, it ended up being a lot closer than we thought. Around off, Shaan looks to play the reverse sweep but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud shout but turned down. It is reviewed but it remains umpire's call on impact. England do not lose a review.

OUCH! That must have hurt! Ali is in pain! Shorter and on the body, Ali looks to pull but is through the shot. It hits his back-hand which has no protection. Ali does complete the run as it rolls towards the off side but is in pain.
On the body, this is pulled through square leg for one.
On the shorter side, this is blocked on the off side.

FOUR! That is excellent placement and so well controlled! There were three men for the pull shot. A deep backward square leg and a deep square leg and also a fine leg. This is short again, Masood just gets on top of the bounce and plays it between them for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Mark Wood gets Shan Masood! He has been bounced out. Masood was playing the short ball so well. He looks to pull again but this time fails to get on top of the bounce. This flies off the top edge and goes towards a very fine fine leg. Jack Leach takes it easily. Masood walks back after getting off to a start. He was looking good but now falls.
Howout: c Jack Leach b Mark Wood

That is brilliantly bowled! He oversteps in the extra effort he put but signs of the ball reverse swinging. This is a yorker, it comes back in from outside off. Has that been taken? Foakes is sure but the soft signal is NOT OUT! ULTRA EDGE SHOWS A SPIKE! By the initial replays, it seems like it has carried. OUT! That is indeed a clean catch and England have a wicket at the stroke of Lunch. The short ball works again. This is on the body, Ali looks to pull, it goes off the glove and towards Foakes who dives forward and takes it. There is an appeal. The umpire is not sure if it carried or not and has a word with his partner. Replays show that it has. Yet another Pakistan batter walks back after getting off to a start. THAT WILL BE LUNCH!
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ollie Robinson

OUT! THAT IS A CLEAN CATCH! That is a superb take from Pope! Rehan Ahmed gets his first Test wicket! A proud, proud moment for him and it is an important wicket as this stand was going along really well. Excellent bowling too. He bowled the googly on the last ball which beat the bat, this time it is the leg spinner, it lands outside off and turns back in nicely. Shakeel looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge, hits the pad and then lobs on the pitch. Pope towards the end, dives forward and takes it with one hand inches above the ground. England appeal but the umpire asks them to wait. He walks to his partner and then takes it upstairs after a chat. Soft signal is OUT! Replays show that is a clean catch. England yet again manage to pick a wicket just as the game was drifting away.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Rehan Ahmed

OUT! AZAM IS RUN OUT! Big, big moment in the game.Flatter and on middle, nudged to the right of square leg. Salman calls for a quick single and Azam is hesitant at first but then runs across. The fielder picks up and throws it to Foakes, the keeper who had to collect on the other side of the stumps. He runs, picks one-handedly and whips the bails off. Babar looked short and the replay confirms but it also shows that Foakes' other hand nudged the bails first, eventually though one bail came off but he managed to remove the other bail quickly with the ball in hand. Harry Brookwith some excellent fielding, Ben Foakeswith a wonderful piece of keeping.
Howout: run out (Harry Brook / Ben Foakes)

OUT! IT IS STOKES WHO HAS TO WALK BACK! Massive confusion and this is the only way this pair could have been broken! The two were looking at so much ease and this is a disastrous start for the visitors after the break. Have to say, it was Brook who was at fault here. This is a full ball, he clips it through mid-wicket. Ali does really well. He makes a lot of ground to his left, dives and pushes it back in. The batters have ran two till then. Both start off for the third but Brook turns back from halfway. Stokes keeps on running. Ali throws it to the bowler who makes no mistake in collecting it and then knocks the bails off. They do go upstairs to check if the stop is clean first which is fine and then who is the one who is run out and replays show it is Stokes! He shows the thumps up to Brook as he walks back which is a good gesture but pretty sure he will be fuming from within. Both Stokes and Azam have been run out in this game so far. Pakistan's 304 nnow looks far away.
Howout: run out (Azhar Ali / Mohammad Wasim)
